  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology for its voice calls, which relies on the LTE network. VoLTE allows voice calls to be made over the 4G network, providing better call quality and connectivity compared to traditional 2G or 3G networks. \n\nSo, while it doesn't require a separate internet connection (like Wi-Fi), it does require access to the 4G LTE network to make voice calls. If you're in an area with strong 4G LTE coverage, you can make and receive calls without any issues. If the 4G LTE network is not available, Jio's services may fall back on older networks (like 2G or 3G) if supported, but the voice call quality and connectivity might not be as good.",
